Transformations introduced were very good. The content division was also good. However, some of the concepts were very complex and were taught without any background which make it difficult for students from other backgrounds, such as mechanical engineering, difficult to understand. Also, another issue was the linking of previous lecture to the next. The lecture videos did not tell much at the start specifically which previous concept was being explained or extended. We had to figure it out on our own the previous concept to which the professor was referring to. A brief recap could be good for the lecture videos.
